  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Preheat</strong> the oven to 180&deg;C/ 160&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the rice, coriander seeds and a large pinch of salt to a medium pot over a high heat with 500ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span> cold water</p>\r\n<p><strong>Bring</strong> to the boil and cook for 25-30 min or until tender with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p><strong>Drain</strong> and return to the pot, covered, until&nbsp;later</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, zest the lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> then cut 4<span class=\"text-danger\"> [8]</span> thin slices from the centre<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> and reserve the remaining ends for garnish&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Peel</strong> the ginger (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Chop</strong> the bottom half of the coriander (mainly stalks)&nbsp;finely, saving the leaves for a later step</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Grind</strong> the lime zest, ginger, half the coriander,&nbsp;a pinch of salt and pepper and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> vegetable oil&nbsp;in a pestle and mortar to form a paste</p>\r\n<p><strong>Tip:</strong> If you don't have a pestle and mortar, chop everything&nbsp;very finely and mix with vegetable oil</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Place</strong> the fish onto a lightly oiled baking tray (use tin foil to avoid a mess)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Spread</strong> the&nbsp;lime/ginger paste&nbsp;over the fish</p>\r\n<p><strong>Top</strong> each fillet with 2&nbsp;lime slices</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Cook</strong> the fish on the top rack for 8-10 min or until the lime slices are beginning to brown</p>\r\n<p><strong>Tip:</strong> Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, chop&nbsp;the pineapple finely</p>\r\n<p><strong>Chop</strong> the remaining coriander (mainly leaves) roughly</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Once</strong> the rice has been cooked and drained, add the pineapple and the remaining coriander</p>\r\n<p><strong>Stir</strong> to combine</p>\r\n<p><strong>Taste</strong> for seasoning adding more salt and pepper if needed</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/580.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Serve</strong>&nbsp;the ginger/lime baked fish with your pineapple rice</p>\r\n<p><strong>Squeeze</strong> the remaining lime over the fish</p>\r\n<p><strong>Enjoy!</strong></p>",
